article.headline: Starbucks bringing back Pumpkin Spice Latte for 17th year
article.body: Starbucks SBUX, +0.53% said Tuesday that it's bringing back its popular Pumpkin Spice Latte for the 17th year in the U.S. and Canada. The beverage, which Starbucks has reported selling 424 million times since 2003, is part of its fall menu that includes Pumpkin Cream Cold Brew as well as pumpkin-flavored cream cheese muffins and scones. Starbucks shares have fallen 10.5% this year, compared to the 6.2% gain for the S&P 500 SPX, +0.87%.
